# Voice Interface Guidelines

- Implement voice interfaces with WebRTC for audio streaming
- Ensure proper audio visualization and feedback during recording
- Implement clear user feedback mechanisms for voice interactions
- Use the Web Audio API for voice recording and processing
- Ensure proper handling of microphone permissions
- Provide fallback text input when voice recognition fails
- Implement proper error handling for voice recognition issues
- Use consistent voice interaction patterns across the application
- Ensure voice interface components are accessible
- Implement proper silence detection and auto-completion
- Use visual cues to indicate recording status
- Ensure voice data is handled securely and with proper privacy considerations
- Implement voice recognition with appropriate feedback mechanisms
- Use consistent voice prompt patterns